JobDescription: We seek a highly experienced Manager, Visual Effects to manage productions across our growing slate of Netflix Franchise Series and Films being managed in the UK. The applicant should be highly regarded and very well established in the VFX industry. The ideal candidate will have held both a significant position with one or more vendors and had client-side production experience. Working alongside our internal creative and production teams, key to the position is the ability to curate VFX vendor and crew talent relations, review and help inform budgets and schedules from pitches, treatments and scripts, creatively assess and comment on work, and support our production partners and filmmakers. You will also be expected to excel as a cross-functional communicator within Netflix and be an ambassador for visual effects.
JobResponsibility: The successful candidate will be self-motivated, proactive, quick-thinking, flexible, able to pivot when necessary, thorough and able to juggle multiple and diverse responsibilities with a strong emphasis on organization and an unwavering attention to detail at all times. This is a demanding and fast moving position that requires someone who is able to exercise good judgment under pressure and shows initiative with a forward-thinking positive attitude to new technologies and workflows.

JobDescription: This new position is a hybrid of renewable energy engineering, technical training, and ownership of residential product installation within the UK. The role will be at the forefront of new product launches, will work closely with our partner network and will ensure that our renewable storage products are installed and commissioned to the highest standards. The role can be based anywhere in the UK and will be a key part of our Energy Operations team (based in Amsterdam). Travel will be required. The team is looking for someone with a strong understanding of solar and energy storage, along with solid electrical engineering skills and in-depth knowledge of code requirements and installation practices for residential and commercial applications.

EducationalRequirements: Master degree / Bachelor degree to complete any reputational university

JobDescription: As a Tech Lead for the team's machine learning work you will be responsible for driving specific projects, setting technical strategy for the team's ML work and empowering more junior members of the team. The role requires partnering with engineers, product managers and other data scientists across the org, and a successful candidate will be able to influence these technical and non-technical partners in order to achieve the best outcome for Airbnb and its customers. A key to success in this role will be to proactively search out opportunities for innovation across data science. Airbnb has a rich set of problems where technical innovation can have high returns. We've identified many of those, but we expect the right candidates to continue this process.
JobResponsibility: Developing integrated trust and risk signals (e.g. embeddings, clustering) that be leveraged across multiple defences Finding opportunities for step changes in model architecture -- e.g. leveraging Graph Neural Networks for applications with Trust, Payments and CS Development of NLP-derived signals to use across the company Utilizing Deep Learning techniques for advanced feature engineering and model building, e.g., how to model for user behaviour sequences, or how can we detect anomalies effectively Devising optimization models to make optimal business decisions while minimizing risk Innovating modelling frameworks in this adversarial setup, e.g., how can models collaboratively surface more risks, or how can models adapt to emerging patterns quickly.
